[{"id":"VR023630","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents three circuit diagrams, labeled X, Y, and Z. Each of the diagrams contain 3 capacitors and a battery. In circuit X, the top side contains 2 capacitors. Moving down the circuit, there are 2 horizontal branches. The first horizontal branch contains another capacitor, and the second horizontal branch contains a battery. In circuit Y, the top side contains 3 capacitors. The bottom side contains a battery. In circuit Z, the left side contains a battery. Moving to the right across the circuit, there are 3 vertical branches. Each of the three vertical branches contains a single capacitor.\" height=\"104\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VR023630.g01.png\" width=\"365\" /></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">The figures above show three circuits, each containing the same battery and identical capacitors. Which circuit has the largest stored charge when it reaches steady state?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR023630_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"X\"><math alttext=\"X\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>X</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Y\"><math alttext=\"Y\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>Y</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Z\"><math alttext=\"Z\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>Z</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">All three store the same charge.</p>"],"answer":2}]